race.comment: LOVEY DOVEY (5) progressed nicely second-up, beaten just 1.5 lengths over 1630m at Doomben. Finds a much more suitable contest and can find winning form for the Waller yard. DEEP DRIVE (4) improved to score here this grade/trip, improving again. Map well enough, and she looks capable of repeating the dose. WHISKY TRAIN (12) was beaten 2.2L in the same contest and was even better at the Gold Coast prior. Hits this at peak and the 3kg claim brings him into it again. MR O'REILLY (1) resumed here in a 65 over 1400m and needed the outing. He's proven second-up and should be ready for the step-up in trip. Draws inside, and he showed plenty of talent early doors. GOOGAZ (3) has been going well in the country, and the blinkers come off. Gets some weight relief with the 2kg claim and should be around the mark.
